==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Electro-vital
<hw>E*lec`tro-vi"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Derived from,
or dependent upon, vital processes; -- said of certain electric currents
supposed by some physiologists to circulate in the nerves of
animals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electro-vitalism</ent>⟦br⟧
